###sequence of files bash loads to set PATH variable

For interactive login shells:
* /etc/profile
* First matched in order of: ~/.bash_profile, ~/.bash_login, ~/.profile 
* On shell termination: ~/.bash_logout

For interactive non-login shells:
* /private/etc/bashrc (usually /etc/bash.bashrc in Linux)
* ~/.bashrc

---------------------------------------------------------------

####/etc/profile >>> ~/.bash_profile >>> ~/.bash_login >>> ~/.profile >>> ~/.bash_logout


.bashrc, .zshrc, or .profile or .bash_profile or .profile

--------------------------------------------------------------------

nano ~/.bashrc

export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-11-openjdk-amd64  # change the path as per your Java version
export PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH

source ~/.bashrc

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Adding a Path to the Linux PATH Variable

